South African retail sales beat estimates and grew the most in seven months in November as specials offered by retailers boosted trade. Sales increased 2.6% from a year earlier compared with a revised 0.4% growth in October, Pretoria-based Statistics South Africa said in a statement on its website on Wednesday. The median estimate of nine economists was for 0.7% growth. <img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-335248" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/South-Africa-Black-Friday-sales-640x359.jpeg" alt="South Africa Black Friday sales" width="640" height="359" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/South-Africa-Black-Friday-sales-640x359.jpeg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/South-Africa-Black-Friday-sales-600x337.jpeg 600w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/South-Africa-Black-Friday-sales-768x431.jpeg 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/South-Africa-Black-Friday-sales.jpeg 814w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" />